{% block body %}
<h1>Engine Architecture</h1>

<p>The Wisp template engine is a high-performance templating system designed for security and speed.</p>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Input</strong>: Template string + data map</li>
  <li><strong>Cache</strong>: Check if template already parsed</li>
  <li><strong>Lexer</strong>: Tokenize template into tokens</li>
  <li><strong>Parser</strong>: Convert tokens to AST</li>
  <li><strong>Scope</strong>: Create variable scope</li>
  <li><strong>Evaluator</strong>: Execute AST with data</li>
  <li><strong>Output</strong>: Rendered string</li>
</ol>

<h2>Rendering Pipeline</h2>

<h3>Caching</h3>
<p>Parsed ASTs are cached in memory:</p>
<pre><code>e.RenderString(template, data)
e.RenderString(template, differentData)</code></pre>

<h3>Security</h3>
<p>Auto-escaping is enabled by default:</p>
<pre><code>e := engine.New()
e.SetAutoEscape(false)</code></pre>

<h3>Resource Limits</h3>
<pre><code>e.SetMaxIterations(10000)</code></pre>

<h2>Performance</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Template caching - avoid re-parsing</li>
  <li>Scope pooling - reduce allocations</li>
  <li>Thread-safe - use across goroutines</li>
</ul>

